Yes it does. By Newtonian laws a uniform sphere attracts as if all the
mass were concentrated at the center. In GR attraction is towards a
point some distance away from the center. In the case of the Sun this
is 27km. This is independent of how dense the Sun is. In the extreme
case where the Sun is 27km in radius we have an event horizon. This is
the way it works.

If you hae a mass at the center you have a nice elliptical Keplerian
orbit which does not precess. With a mass displaced onto a virtual
sphere you get precession.

